---
import { Layout } from "/layouts/layout.squirrel";
const title = "Learn about pages";
---
<Layout>
    <h1>${title}</h1>

    <p>To create a new page create into folder "/backend/pages".

    Pages have a head and a body. The head has the script part and the body the template.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-2">Page</h4>

    <pre class="code" data-lang="Page"><code>---
head (ES6 script)
---
body (HTML with ES6 template literals)
</code></pre>

<h4>Example</h4>

    <pre class="code" data-lang="Page"><code>---
const title = "New page"
---
<h1>\$\{title\}</h1>
<p>Some text</p></code></pre>

</Layout>
